sql:
SELECT user_id, COUNT(DISTINCT gps_location) AS distinct_gps_locations
FROM sensor_data
GROUP BY user_id;

external_knowledge:
- 'end-users' refer to non-administrative users who are the primary wearers of devices;
- 'fall detected' is an alert type indicating a potential fall has been detected by the device;
- 'health metric ratio' refers to the proportion of health metrics with a value greater than 100, indicating potentially significant health data;
- 'recognized with high confidence' means the device was confident (confidence > 0.75) in its activity recognition.

sql:
SELECT sd.data_id, sd.activity, sd.timestamp, at.activity_name
FROM sensor_data sd
JOIN activity_types at ON sd.activity = at.activity_id;

SELECT health_metrics.metric_name, health_metrics.value, users.user_id, users.username
FROM health_metrics
JOIN users ON health_metrics.user_id = users.user_id;
